Info
widgets_values:
====================
 JPS Workflow v14.0
====================

5 Generation Modes (blue nodes)
===============================

- TXT2IMG
- IMG2IMG
- Canny Control Net
- Depth Control Net
- Inpainting

Strength and Ctrl-Options are not used by TXT2IMG.

Ctrl-Options are not used by IMG2IMG and Inpainting.

To some extend you can control how much inpainting is trying to fix the results by changing steps and base percentage. So if you get artefacts on the border of the masked area try changing those values.

For Inpainting use "Open Mask Editor" in the context menu of "Generation Input Image". High "strength_percent" values (default = 100) are best for consistent Inpainting results.


Revision (brown nodes)
======================

- ON/OFF Switch for Revision #1 and #2.
- Option to turn ON/OFF Positive/Negative TXT Prompts

All Options are only active if Revision #1 is turned ON. Using only Revision #2 gives inconsistent results or errors.


Image Adapter (yellow nodes)
============================

- ON/OFF Switch for IP Adapter #1 and #2.

Results are best if you keep close to square aspect ratio. Extreme ratios like 21:9 or 9:21 don't work well.

Options are only active if the corresponding Image Adapter Mode is turned ON.


Additional Features
===================

- 2 variants (Base + Refiner / Base Only) with adjustable refiner percentage
- Upscaled versions of the 2 variants
- Style options (SAI presets + artists + movie titles)
- Up to 5x Lora
- Use resolution from settings or input image
- Disable parts of the workflow (for example Base Only, Base + Refiner, Upscaler)

You may disable parts of the workflow by turning on/off output images in the menu area. Upscaled versions need the lower resolution image as starting point. Disabling only the standard resolution will result in errors. 

You can switch between resolution from settings or input image. The resolution from input image will adjust the image to the closest recommended SDXL resolution.


Required nodes, models and other files
======================================

All required nodes should be available through ComfyUI Manager:

* Mikey Nodes (for save and prompt)
* rgthree's ComfyUi Nodes (for output switch and better seed control)
* ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus (for IP-Adapter)
* ComfyUI's ControlNet Auxiliary Preprocessors (for Revision)
* JPS Custom Nodes for ComfyUI

SDXL Base Model:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0/blob/main/sd_xl_base_1.0_0.9vae.safetensors

SDXL Refiner:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-refiner-1.0/blob/main/sd_xl_refiner_1.0_0.9vae.safetensors

Upscaler: 
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-NMKD-Superscale

Revision / Clip Vision (also used by IP-Adapter) - copy to ComfyUI\models\clip_vision:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/clip_vision_g/blob/main/clip_vision_g.safetensors

IP-Adapter Models - copy to ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus\models:
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/blob/main/sdxl_models/ip-adapter_sdxl.bin

Inpainting:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/stable-diffusion-xl-1.0-inpainting-0.1/blob/main/unet/diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16.safetensors

Control Net:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-zoe-depth-sdxl-1.0/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-canny-sdxl-1.0/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16.safetensors


Additional Info
===============

It's recommended to change "Link Render Mode" to "Straight" or "Hidden" for a better user experience, if you don't want to edit the workflow. 

You have to change some nodes (models, images) to your own filenames, when you first use this workflow.
